sentences: Laurie Lewis (born September 28, 1950 in Long Beach, California), is an American singer and bluegrass musician.
Lewis fell in love with American folk music as a teenager, at the sunset of the 1960s folk revival.

In the early 1970s she played with The Phantoms of the Opry, a Bay Area bluegrass band that also included Pat Enright (later of the Nashville Bluegrass Band).
In 1979 she founded the Grant Street String Band, also including Beth Weil, Tom Bekeny, Greg Townsend, and Steve Krouse, in which her own songwriting came to the forefront.
In the late 1980s, she formed "Laurie Lewis and Grant Street".

Nowadays, she often plays under different names with a fairly regular roster of musicians, calling themselves "Laurie Lewis and her Bluegrass Pals," "the Guest House Band;"  in 2006, she renamed her group "Laurie Lewis and the Right Hands."
